# سُراد | Sorad — Streaming Platform Workspace

## Overview

pnpm workspace monorepo — Arabic video streaming platform (سُراد / Sorad).

## Stack

- **Monorepo tool**: pnpm workspaces
- **Node.js version**: 24
- **Package manager**: pnpm
- **TypeScript version**: 5.9
- **API framework**: Express 5
- **Database**: PostgreSQL (Replit built-in) with raw pg queries
- **Validation**: Zod (`zod/v4`), `drizzle-zod`
- **API codegen**: Orval (from OpenAPI spec)
- **Build**: esbuild (CJS bundle)
- **Auth**: JWT + bcryptjs
- **Frontend**: React 18 + Vite + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui
- **Video**: hls.js for HLS playback
- **i18n**: i18next + react-i18next (Arabic RTL primary, English secondary)
- **Fonts**: Cairo (Arabic glyph support)

## Platform Features

- Full HLS adaptive bitrate streaming with hls.js
- JWT authentication with bcryptjs password hashing
- Bilingual Arabic/English UI with RTL support
- Premium content subscription model
- Stream token generation (simulated signed URLs)
- Admin panel: full content CRUD
- Network resilience: quality adaptation based on connection
- Analytics events tracking (play_start, buffering, quality_switch, etc.)
- Service Worker for HLS manifest caching
- Rate limiting on auth and stream-token endpoints

## Structure

```text
workspace/
├── artifacts/
│   ├── api-server/      # Express API server (PORT assigned by Replit)
│   └── sorad-web/       # React + Vite web client (preview at /)
├── lib/
│   ├── api-spec/        # OpenAPI 3.1 spec + Orval codegen config
│   ├── api-client-react/ # Generated React Query hooks
│   ├── api-zod/         # Generated Zod schemas
│   └── db/              # Drizzle schema (not heavily used; API uses raw pg)
├── .env.example         # Environment variable template
└── README.md            # Full docs with test credentials
```

